SIMPLE: double-quick
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Double-quick
<hw>Dou"ble-quick`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>Of, or performed in, the fastest time or step in marching, next to
the run; <as>as, a <ex>double-quick</ex> step or march</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Double-quick</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Double-quick
<hw>Dou"ble-quick`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Double-quick time, step, or
march.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Double-quick time requires 165 steps, each 33 inches in
length, to be taken in one minute. The number of steps may be increased
up to 180 per minute.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Double-quick</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Double-quick
<hw>Dou"ble-quick`</hw>, <pos>v. i. & t.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>To
move, or cause to move, in double-quick time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doubler</ent>⟦br⟧
